    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for model risk level 3. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given the standardized nature of ASTM F1717 and the regulatory precedent for single-condition acceptance testing of spinal fixation constructs. Overall credibility is assessed as sufficient to support the intended regulatory use. Note: this package conforms to the Minimal profile and does not include a structured ContextOfUse object; the intended use scope is described narratively in the package description.",
